{"nodes": [{"id": "2026_05_27_add_vim_mode_extension_design_document", "label": "Design", "file_type": "document", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-05-27-add-vim-mode-extension/design.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "2026_05_27_add_vim_mode_extension_design_context", "label": "Context", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-05-27-add-vim-mode-extension/design.md", "source_location": "line 1", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "`pi-vimmode` is currently a minimal Bun/TypeScript package with no extension entrypoint. Pi supports custom editor replacement through `ctx.ui.setEditorComponent()` and `CustomEditor`. The extension must operate inside Pi's prompt editor, not as an input transform, because Vim behavior needs per-key modal state before prompt submission. Pi editor constraints shape the implementation:"}, {"id": "2026_05_27_add_vim_mode_extension_design_goals_non_goals", "label": "Goals / Non-Goals", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-05-27-add-vim-mode-extension/design.md", "source_location": "line 12", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "**Goals:** - Provide a working Pi extension that installs/loads as a package and replaces the main prompt editor."}, {"id": "2026_05_27_add_vim_mode_extension_design_decisions", "label": "Decisions", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-05-27-add-vim-mode-extension/design.md", "source_location": "line 29", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "### Use `CustomEditor` as the integration layer Build `VimEditor extends CustomEditor` and register it on `session_start` with `ctx.ui.setEditorComponent()`."}, {"id": "2026_05_27_add_vim_mode_extension_design_use_customeditor_as_the_integration_layer", "label": "Use CustomEditor as the integration layer", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-05-27-add-vim-mode-extension/design.md", "source_location": "line 31", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Build `VimEditor extends CustomEditor` and register it on `session_start` with `ctx.ui.setEditorComponent()`. Alternatives considered:"}, {"id": "2026_05_27_add_vim_mode_extension_design_prefer_pi_compatibility_over_strict_vim_conflicts", "label": "Prefer Pi compatibility over strict Vim conflicts", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-05-27-add-vim-mode-extension/design.md", "source_location": "line 43", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Insert mode delegates to the default editor. Normal and visual modes intercept only recognized Vim printable commands and pass unknown control/non-printable input to Pi. Conflict choices:"}, {"id": "2026_05_27_add_vim_mode_extension_design_keep_core_text_operations_pure", "label": "Keep core text operations pure", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-05-27-add-vim-mode-extension/design.md", "source_location": "line 55", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Implement buffer helpers for ranges, line deletion/yank/paste, and cursor targets. `VimEditor` owns mode state and calls helpers, then writes text back. Alternatives considered:"}, {"id": "2026_05_27_add_vim_mode_extension_design_restore_cursor_through_public_movement_sequences", "label": "Restore cursor through public movement sequences", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-05-27-add-vim-mode-extension/design.md", "source_location": "line 66", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "After structural `setText()` operations, restore cursor by moving from the post-`setText()` end position to the target position using delegated key sequences (`up`, `home`, `right`). Alternatives considered:"}, {"id": "2026_05_27_add_vim_mode_extension_design_ship_visual_operations_before_visual_highlighting", "label": "Ship visual operations before visual highlighting", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-05-27-add-vim-mode-extension/design.md", "source_location": "line 77", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Visual mode will track an anchor, show a `VISUAL` indicator plus selection summary, and make `y`, `d`/`x`, and `c` operate on the selected range. Full highlighted selection rendering can follow later. Alternatives considered:"}, {"id": "2026_05_27_add_vim_mode_extension_design_risks_trade_offs", "label": "Risks / Trade-offs", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-05-27-add-vim-mode-extension/design.md", "source_location": "line 88", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "- Public cursor restoration is O(lines + columns) after structural edits \u2192 Prompts are small; keep helpers bounded and tested. - Visual selection without full highlight may feel incomplete \u2192 Show clear `VISUAL` mode/status and selection size; add highlight later if needed. - Autocomplete may conflict with normal/visual key handling \u2192 Insert mode delegates fully; non-insert modes should delegate non-printable control sequences and avoid stealing app shortcuts."}, {"id": "2026_05_27_add_vim_mode_extension_design_migration_plan", "label": "Migration Plan", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-05-27-add-vim-mode-extension/design.md", "source_location": "line 96", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "1. Add package metadata, source files, tests, and README in this extension package. 2. Validate with `bun test` and `bun run check-types`. 3. Smoke test locally with Pi loading `./src/index.ts` or package-configured extension path."}, {"id": "2026_05_27_add_vim_mode_extension_design_ref_src_index_ts", "label": "index.ts", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-05-27-add-vim-mode-extension/design.md", "source_location": "line 100", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}], "edges": [{"source": "2026_05_27_add_vim_mode_extension_design_document", "target": "2026_05_27_add_vim_mode_extension_design_context", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-05-27-add-vim-mode-extension/design.md", "source_location": "line 1", "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "2026_05_27_add_vim_mode_extension_design_document", "target": "2026_05_27_add_vim_mode_extension_design_goals_non_goals", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-05-27-add-vim-mode-extension/design.md", "source_location": "line 12", "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "2026_05_27_add_vim_mode_extension_design_document", "target": "2026_05_27_add_vim_mode_extension_design_decisions", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-05-27-add-vim-mode-extension/design.md", "source_location": "line 29", "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "2026_05_27_add_vim_mode_extension_design_document", "target": "2026_05_27_add_vim_mode_extension_design_use_customeditor_as_the_integration_layer", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-05-27-add-vim-mode-extension/design.md", "source_location": "line 31", "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "2026_05_27_add_vim_mode_extension_design_document", "target": "2026_05_27_ad